node.text: This incredible Yacht was built by the German yard Lurssen. She was designed by Espen Oeino and Mark Berryman. She’s 136 Meters (446 feet) long and 20.5 meters (67 feet) wide! Her 11 luxurious cabins hold 22 guest with 25 cabins accommodating 54 crew. She has 12000 horsepower and can run 6500 miles without refueling. Some of her epic options include, heated floors, theater, gym, 5 tenders, flyboards, seabobs, waverunners, windsurfers, motorbikes, and of course a submarine. Her swimming pool can change from jacuzzi hot to ice cold in 10 minutes. The full service spa features a cryosauna and steam room. The rumor is that the Yacht is owned by Jeff Bezos. I don’t think so as she’s available for charter and I don’t think the richest man in the world would need to rent his Yacht out. The rumored charter price is $1.5 Million a week. (Plus fuel/food/alcohol and tip approx $2 Million total) She cost almost $400 Million to build and requires about $2.5 Million a week to operate. Gather 22 of your closest friends, have them pitch in $90k each for the week and have the trip of a lifetime!
